Paper: hep-th/9701144

Date: 1997-01-27

Title: On the Space-Time Uncertainty Relations of Liouville Strings and D

BranesAuthors: G. Amelino-Camelia, J. Ellis, N.E. Mavromatos, and D.V. Nanopoulos

Comments: 8 pages, LaTex

Journal-ref: Mod.Phys.Lett. A12 (1997) 2029-2036

Within a Liouville approach to non-critical string theory, we argue for anon-trivial commutation relation between space and time observables, leading toa non-zero space-time uncertainty relation $\delta x \delta t > 0$, whichvanishes in the limit of weak string coupling.